======================================================================
PART 5: KEY THEOREM TEST
======================================================================
For each non-TT 2-path (a,b,c) with c→a (i.e., 3-cycle a→b→c→a),
find ALL other non-TT 2-paths sharing a non-allowed face with (a,b,c).
The difference of two such paths is in Ω_3 if they share the same bad face.
  Bad-face group sizes (how many non-TT paths share same bad face):
    size 1: 4320 groups
    size 2: 1440 groups
    size 3: 160 groups

Key: if group size ≥ 2, pairwise differences are in Ω_3
(because the non-allowed face cancels).
This provides (size-1) independent Ω_3 elements per group.

Done.
